1. Preliminary per-task Activity.log format description.
  Activity.log is a human-readable (text) file and
  it contains one line per message state change:
  STATE,MSGID,SUBSID,LASTTIME,TIMELEFT,TEXTID,SMPP,USERDATA
    where the fields are (separated with single comma):
  STATE - one-digit [1..9] integer: representation of the current state
          (to be specified);
  MSGID - uint64 [1..]: unique (per-task) message id;
  SUBSID - uint64: subscriber number (only the part w/o .ton.npi);
  LASTTIME - uint32: absolute time(2) in seconds of the message state change;
  TIMELEFT - int32: TTL of the message in seconds;
  TEXTID - uint32 [1..]: message text id in glossary;
  SMPP - int32: smpp error code or 0;
  USERDATA - ASCII-string: up to 23 bytes, should not contain
            special chars and comma, enclosed in quotes;
  Example:
3,556,79131234567,1285303430,600,13,0,"msg0x778899"
